].
Crews do not experience the aforementioned stressors independently; therefore, it is important to consider the combined effects of these space environment threats on human physiology, psychology, and performance. These stressful conditions, collectively referred to as “the space exposome” [
6
], may also exacerbate complex health problems in astronauts embarking on long-duration missions [
